OL,5, A police force has apologised after    
OL,6, using an image of a black person       
OL,7, dealing drugs in an anti-drugs leaflet.
OL,9,FCumbria Constabulary said it accepted  
OL,10,Fit used a poor choice of image in the  
OL,11,Fleaflet, which appealed for information
OL,12,Fabout crimes.                          
OL,14,FCampaigning organisation Anti Racist   
OL,15,FCumbria said the image perpetuated     
OL,16,F"racist stereotypes" and some black    
OL,17,Fpeople felt "watched".                 
OL,19,FThe force said the leaflet had been    
OL,20,Fwithdrawn from circulation.            
